reviewText: This show is one of my favorites since it came out. It has the perfect formula to be a good one, but it's getting old the same thing all the time.Season four shows us a more mature cast, like Serena stopping dating random guys, Blair finally leaving Chuck (for good), and Dan finally finding his own way without Serena, Vanessa being a little more independent, and Jenny just messing up with Blair (but she only appeared like in 4 episodes in the whole season). But what about Nate? He didn't had strong plots... he was just there filling some minutes of the 42 minute episodes. I hope that season five gives Chace the opportunity to show a good work as Nate, as he was in season one.Anyway, the show keeps being good but I hope it shows something new at the beginning of the new season, because it has the qualities to be a show to remember.

Serena is just a Sunshine and guys like that. Blair and Chuck had some intense moments. Dan is usual slutty-self. Cant figure out what he wants. If you like fashion, you will enjoy the movie. If you after the story and learning some valuable lessons, then....try " The O.C" - this one has alot to teach you. Especially family values.

reviewText: Paris! do i need to say more? i love that they filmed in Paris it fits Blair so well! and there's a prince! a real one... nice.This season was great, if you are a gossip girl fan you will like it because it has everything: drama, fights,gossip, love, hate, confusions, and of course the best part of the show CHUCK & BLAIRChuck tries with Eva but ends, Blair has an insignificant thing with Dan( ew ew ew) but thank God it goes no where ( admit it they don't belong together).Chuck and Blair start messing around ( funny) but then Blair wants to be like Hillary Clinton as secretary of state not as Clinton's wife ( she said it like this lol) which means she wants to succeed and her own fame she doesn't not want to be thought of just because of Chuck. Blair focus on her goals and lands a job intership at a fashion magazine.Chuck has a brief romance with another chick but ends ( forgot her name).Jenny is finally GONE after this season which makes me happy she was on like 2 episodes only i think =). Serena of course has more than one lover in this season that's nothing new( i love how she falls for various men every single season) but never really deciding between Nate and Dan.Serena and Blair are going to Columbia and living together which is nice their friendship is just getting stronger.Dan feels something for blair, then Serena again -_- idk i dont really like dan lately also nate both characters need to improve all they live for is Serena or random girls they need a life!Well well the best of this season is Paris, Chucks empire in jeopardy,Blair n chuck being friends with benefits, Blair working ( it was entertaining),the prince and Blair! and the last episode omg!!!!!who is pregnant? I know... just about to marry a prince when Chuck left a seed -_- OMG
